Package stochasticShortestPath

Class Reproduction

  • java.lang.Object
    • stochasticShortestPath.StochasticEvent
      • stochasticShortestPath.Reproduction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Event

    class Reproduction
extends StochasticEvent
    The class Reproduction is a subclass of StochasticEvent. When simulated, a Reproduction brings a new individual to the population. Reproduction instances have a timestamp that is defined by the sum of the current time of the simulation with a number drawn from an exponential distribution.
    Author:
    ManuelSerraNunes

    • Constructor Detail

      • Reproduction

        Reproduction​(Individual ind)
        Reproduction constructor. It associates the Reproduction with an Individual. It also computes the time of the move by adding the currentTime of the simulation where the reproduction takes place at the time the reproduction is created with a number drawn from an exponential distribution. If the time of the reproduction is posterior to the death time of the associated Individual the time is set to -1.
        Parameters:
        ind - the Individual that will reproduce.

    • Method Detail

      • simulateEvent

        public void simulateEvent​()
        When a reproduction is simulated the next reproduction of the individual is added to the PEC. Then, the individual creates it's child. The child's first move, first reproduction and death are added to the PEC.
